# Entry Note Structure Prompt

Generate an Entry note (synthesis/analysis) for the following source.

## Source Data
- Title: {{TITLE}}
- Source Filename: {{SOURCE_FILENAME}}
- URL: {{URL}}
- Source Type: {{SOURCE_TYPE}}
- Author: {{AUTHOR}}
- Language: {{LANGUAGE}}
- Template: {{TEMPLATE}}
- Tags: {{TAGS}}

## Extracted Content
{{CONTENT}}

## Insights (if available)
{{INSIGHTS}}

## OUTPUT FORMAT

Generate the full markdown file content including YAML frontmatter and body.

Frontmatter rules:
- title: same as source title
- source: wikilink to source note "[[filename]]"
- source_url: full URL
- type: source type
- author: author
- date_entry: today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format
- status: review
- template: the template type
- tags: always include "entry", then the topic tags
- language: (only if not "en")

Body rules based on template:

**CRITICAL: NEVER generate stub content, TODO placeholders, or empty sections. Every section must contain substantive, meaningful analysis derived from the source.**

### standard template
Sections:
- ## Summary
- ## Core insights  
- ## Other takeaways
- ## Diagrams (mark "n/a" if none)
- ## Open questions
- ## Linked concepts (list wikilinks to concept notes)

### technical template
Sections:
- ## Key Findings
- ## Data/Evidence
- ## Methodology
- ## Limitations
- ## Linked concepts

### chinese template
Sections (in Chinese):
- ## 摘要
- ## 核心发现
- ## 其他要点
- ## 图表 (mark "n/a" if none)
- ## 开放问题
- ## 关联概念

For Summary/摘要: provide a 1-2 sentence high-level summary.
For Core insights/核心发现: extract ALL significant insights, findings, arguments, claims, and observations — no limit. Prioritize depth and completeness.
For Other takeaways/其他要点: extract secondary insights, interesting quotes, counter-arguments, or edge cases.
For Linked concepts: list wikilinks to related concept notes (from plan).

Output ONLY the markdown file content, no explanation.
